In the Desert<br /><div style="text-align: left;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; by Stephen Crane</div><br /> <br />In the desert<br />I saw a creature, naked, bestial,<br />Who, squatting upon the ground,<br />Held his heart in his hands,<br />And ate of it.<br />I said, &quot;Is it good, friend?&quot;<br />&quot;It is bitter &ndash; bitter&quot;, he answered,<br />&quot;But I like it<br />Because it is bitter,<br />And because it is my heart.&quot;

